---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service | Amplified Generative AI Innovation Center">
	<Header />
	
	<main class="pt-16 lg:pt-20">
		<!-- Hero Section -->
		<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 py-20">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
				<h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
					Please read these terms carefully before using our services, platforms, and educational content.
				</p>
				<div class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">
					Effective Date: December 2024
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Terms Content -->
		<section class="py-20 bg-white">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
					
					<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-500 mb-12">
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Important Notice</h2>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							By accessing or using our website, research platforms, training programs, or services, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
						</p>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">1. About Our Services</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-6">The Amplified Generative AI Innovation Center at Vanderbilt University provides:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-2">
						<li><strong>Research and Publications:</strong> Academic research, papers, and intellectual contributions to the field of augmented intelligence</li>
						<li><strong>Educational Content:</strong> Online courses, training programs, and educational materials through platforms like Coursera</li>
						<li><strong>Technology Platforms:</strong> The Amplify Generative AI Platform and related tools for academic and research use</li>
						<li><strong>Consulting and Advisory Services:</strong> Professional services for organizations and government entities</li>
						<li><strong>Public Information:</strong> Website content, news, and thought leadership materials</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">2. Acceptable Use</h2>
					
					<div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
						<h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-3">You may use our services for:</h4>
						<ul class="text-green-700 space-y-1">
							<li>• Educational and research purposes</li>
							<li>• Professional development and training</li>
							<li>• Academic collaboration and inquiry</li>
							<li>• Legitimate business and organizational needs</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
						<h4 class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-3">You may NOT use our services to:</h4>
						<ul class="text-red-700 space-y-1">
							<li>• Violate any laws or regulations</li>
							<li>• Infringe on intellectual property rights</li>
							<li>• Distribute malware or harmful content</li>
							<li>• Engage in unauthorized data collection or harvesting</li>
							<li>• Interfere with or disrupt our services</li>
							<li>• Impersonate others or provide false information</li>
							<li>• Use our content for commercial purposes without permission</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">3. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
					
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Our Content</h3>
					<p class="mb-6">
						All content on this website, including but not limited to text, graphics, logos, research papers, course materials, and software, is owned by Vanderbilt University or the Amplified Generative AI Innovation Center and is protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Research and Publications</h3>
					<p class="mb-6">
						Our research papers and academic publications are typically made available under academic fair use guidelines. Proper attribution is required when citing or referencing our work. Commercial use requires explicit permission.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Course Materials</h3>
					<p class="mb-8">
						Course content delivered through Coursera and other platforms is subject to the terms of those platforms as well as our intellectual property rights. Students may use materials for personal learning but may not redistribute or commercialize content.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">4. User Accounts and Registration</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-4">For certain services, you may need to create an account or register. When you do:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-2">
						<li>You must provide accurate and complete information</li>
						<li>You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials</li>
						<li>You are responsible for all activities that occur under your account</li>
						<li>You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized use</li>
						<li>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-4">Our services integrate with third-party platforms and services, including:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li><strong>Coursera:</strong> Online course delivery and enrollment</li>
						<li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Website analytics and performance monitoring</li>
						<li><strong>Email Services:</strong> Communication and newsletter delivery</li>
						<li><strong>Cloud Providers:</strong> Hosting and infrastructure services</li>
					</ul>

					<p class="mb-8">
						Your use of these third-party services is governed by their respective terms of service and privacy policies. We are not responsible for the practices or policies of third-party services.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">6. Disclaimers and Limitations</h2>
					
					<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Service Availability</h4>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							We strive to maintain high service availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted access to our services. We may perform maintenance, updates, or modifications that temporarily affect service availability.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Educational Content</h4>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							Our educational content is provided for informational and educational purposes. While we strive for accuracy, we do not warrant that all information is complete, current, or error-free.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Research and Experimental Technologies</h4>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							Some of our services may include experimental technologies or research prototypes. These are provided "as is" and may not be suitable for production use.
						</p>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-8">
						To the fullest extent permitted by law, Vanderbilt University and the Amplified Generative AI Innovation Center shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profits, data, or business opportunities, arising from your use of our services.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">8. Academic Integrity and Research Ethics</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-4">When using our services for academic or research purposes:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 space-y-2">
						<li>You must maintain the highest standards of academic integrity</li>
						<li>Proper attribution and citation are required when using our research or content</li>
						<li>Plagiarism or misrepresentation of our work is strictly prohibited</li>
						<li>Research collaborations must comply with ethical research standards</li>
						<li>Any use of AI tools must be disclosed appropriately in academic work</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">9. Government and Compliance</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-6">
						As part of Vanderbilt University, we comply with applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations. Our services are subject to U.S. export control laws and regulations.
					</p>

					<p class="mb-8">
						Users accessing our services from outside the United States are responsible for compliance with local laws and regulations.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">10. Termination</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-6">
						We reserve the right to terminate or suspend access to our services at any time, with or without notice, for any reason, including violation of these terms.
					</p>

					<p class="mb-8">
						Upon termination, your right to use our services ceases immediately. Sections of these terms that by their nature should survive termination shall survive.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">11. Changes to Terms</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-8">
						We may update these Terms of Service periodically. We will notify users of significant changes by posting a notice on our website or through other appropriate means. Continued use of our services after such modifications constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">12. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
					
					<p class="mb-8">
						These Terms of Service are governed by the laws of the State of Tennessee and the United States of America. Any disputes arising from these terms shall be resolved in the appropriate courts of Tennessee.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">13. Contact Information</h2>
					
					<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-purple-50 p-8 rounded-xl">
						<h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Questions about these Terms of Service?</h4>
						<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
							<div>
								<p class="text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong></p>
								<a href="mailto:amplify@vanderbilt.edu" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">amplify@vanderbilt.edu</a>
							</div>
							<div>
								<p class="text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Mail:</strong></p>
								<address class="text-gray-700 not-italic">
									Amplified Generative AI Innovation Center<br>
									Vanderbilt University<br>
									Nashville, TN 37235<br>
									Attn: Legal Affairs
								</address>
							</div>
						</div>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-6">
							For legal matters related to Vanderbilt University, you may also contact the University's Office of General Counsel.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</Layout>